Current pass is routed to native Codex `gpt-5.4` with `xhigh`, and I persisted the decision in [account-routing-decision.md](/home/raed/projects/air-mentor-ui/audit-map/25-accounts-routing/account-routing-decision.md). The selector still returns native for `account-routing-pass`, and a forced non-native probe now correctly pins to the slot’s execution-verified model instead of a higher merely visible one.

I also reconciled a material audit-OS drift: the live slot-status files and execution-smoke artifacts show all six Arctic `codex-*` slots are execution-verified on `gpt-5.3-codex`, while several routing docs still said Arctic Codex execution failed. I updated the routing docs, coverage/memory/reconciliation, current operator reports, and queue, and tightened [select-execution-route.sh](/home/raed/projects/air-mentor-ui/audit-map/16-scripts/select-execution-route.sh) so alternate Arctic routes pin to execution-verified models only.

Key updated files are [current-model-availability.md](/home/raed/projects/air-mentor-ui/audit-map/25-accounts-routing/current-model-availability.md), [provider-model-preferences.md](/home/raed/projects/air-mentor-ui/audit-map/25-accounts-routing/provider-model-preferences.md), [coverage-ledger.md](/home/raed/projects/air-mentor-ui/audit-map/23-coverage/coverage-ledger.md), [working-knowledge.md](/home/raed/projects/air-mentor-ui/audit-map/24-agent-memory/working-knowledge.md), and [contradiction-matrix.md](/home/raed/projects/air-mentor-ui/audit-map/14-reconciliation/contradiction-matrix.md). `pending.queue` now advances to `cost-optimization-pass`.

Residual risk: high-stakes passes remain native-only because Arctic reasoning/thinking control and higher visible tiers like Arctic Codex `gpt-5.4` / `gpt-5.4-mini` are still not separately execution-verified. I also could not cleanly stop the duplicate detached `account-routing-pass` via the tmux wrapper because `tmux has-session` hit `Operation not permitted`, though the checkpoint PID was no longer alive during review.
